  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I log in my Facebook account if you forgot your password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Facebook password, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n### **On the Facebook Website:**\n1. **Go to the Facebook Login Page**: Open your browser and visit [facebook.com](https://www.facebook.com).\n2. **Click \"Forgot Password?\"**: Below the login fields, click on the **\"Forgot Password?\"** link.\n3. **Enter Your Information**: You\u2019ll be asked to enter your email address, phone number, or username associated with your account.\n4. **Search for Your Account**: Facebook will search for your account. If found, you\u2019ll see options to reset your password.\n5. **Choose a Reset Method**:\n   - **Email**: Facebook will send a reset link to your registered email address.\n   - **Phone**: Facebook will send a verification code to your registered phone number.\n6. **Follow the Instructions**: Open the email or text message and follow the link or enter the verification code provided.\n7. **Create a New Password**: After verifying your identity, you\u2019ll be prompted to create a new password.\n\n### **On the Facebook App:**\n1. **Open the Facebook App**.\n2. **Tap \"Forgot Password?\"**: Below the login fields, tap **\"Forgot Password?\"**.\n3. **Enter Your Email or Phone Number**: Enter the email or phone number associated with your account.\n4. **Follow the On-Screen Instructions**: Choose how you want to reset your password (via email, phone, or trusted contacts) and follow the steps.\n\n### **If You Can\u2019t Access Your Email or Phone Number:**\n1. **Try Other Options**: On the reset password page, Facebook may offer alternative methods to verify your identity, such as using a trusted contact or answering security questions.\n2. **Contact Facebook Support**: If you\u2019re unable to reset your password, you can visit Facebook\u2019s **Help Center** at [https://www.facebook.com/help](https://www.facebook.com/help) for additional support.\n\n### **Tips:**\n- Ensure you\u2019re using the correct email address or phone number associated with your account.\n- Check your spam or junk folder if you don\u2019t see the reset email.\n- Create a strong, unique password to secure your account.\n\nIf you\u2019re still having trouble, consider reaching out to Facebook\u2019s support team for further assistance.",
